WEBVTT

00:01.760 --> 00:04.365
***

00:11.410 --> 00:15.073
* YOU CAN SLAM THE DOOR, BABY,
HELP CONTRADICT YOUR MOVE *

00:15.110 --> 00:16.179
WAIT, WAIT!
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

00:16.210 --> 00:17.768
YOU'RE TOUCHING ME!

00:17.810 --> 00:19.675
JUST...
WE CAN'T GO IN YET.

00:19.720 --> 00:21.039
WHY?

00:24.120 --> 00:25.417
ARE YOU
AVOIDING JARVIS?

00:25.450 --> 00:27.509
WHAT? NO! MY...

00:27.560 --> 00:28.515
M-MY FOOT'S ASLEEP.

00:28.560 --> 00:30.824
COPS CAN'T WALK AROUND
WITH ONE FOOT ASLEEP.

00:30.860 --> 00:32.122
DAMN, HIS WIFE'S
PRETTY HOT.

00:32.160 --> 00:36.164
HOW THE HELL DID THAT GUY
GET SUCH A HOT WIFE?
SHE'S INTO COPS.

00:37.970 --> 00:39.164
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

00:40.040 --> 00:41.735
DIAZ, HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?
GAIL...

00:41.770 --> 00:44.659
THAT MARRIED WOMAN
THAT YOU'RE SLEEPING WITH

00:44.710 --> 00:45.768
IS THAT MARRIED WOMAN?

00:45.810 --> 00:47.937
I TRIED TO BREAK IT OFF
LIKE THREE TIMES LAST NIGHT,

00:47.980 --> 00:52.212
BUT THEN SHE DISTRACTED ME,
LIKE...THREE TIMES, FOUR TIMES.

00:52.250 --> 00:53.740
G-GOOD MORNING, SIR.

00:53.780 --> 00:55.748
DIAZ.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

00:55.780 --> 00:57.486
BET YOU
KEEP HER PURRING, HUH?

00:57.520 --> 00:59.181
E-EXCUSE ME?

00:59.220 --> 01:01.484
YOUR TRUCK. WHAT IS THIS --
AN '87, '88?

01:01.520 --> 01:05.923
MY WIFE'S CAR HAS A LEAK.
DO YOU MIND TAKING A LOOK?

01:05.960 --> 01:07.097
NO, NO, SIR.

01:07.130 --> 01:10.293
GREAT.
SHE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.

01:12.700 --> 01:13.735
BREAK IT OFF.

01:17.040 --> 01:18.268
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

01:19.380 --> 01:21.905
THANK YOU, OFFICER. I'M NOT SURE
WHAT THE PROBLEM IS.

01:21.940 --> 01:24.875
DID YOU ASK HIM
TO ASK ME?

01:24.910 --> 01:27.777
I SAID YOU LOOKED LIKE
YOU WERE GOOD WITH YOUR HANDS.

01:27.820 --> 01:30.539
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY, WELL, UH,

01:30.590 --> 01:32.410
POP THE HOOD, AND I'LL --
I'LL HAVE A LOOK.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.712
[ SIREN CHIRPS IN DISTANCE ]

01:39.130 --> 01:40.995
[ SNIFFS ]

01:41.030 --> 01:42.292
[ Quietly ] RELAX.

01:42.330 --> 01:45.720
I DIDN'T TELL HIM I KNEW YOU
WERE GOOD WITH YOUR HANDS.

01:47.040 --> 01:48.894
UH...

01:48.940 --> 01:51.158
YOUR OIL CAP IS LOOSE.

01:51.210 --> 01:54.509
JUST TIGHTEN THAT UP.
IT SHOULD BE AS GOOD AS NEW.

01:54.540 --> 01:58.169
[ Quietly ] GETTING FIRED
IS NOT A TURN-ON.

01:58.210 --> 02:00.110
BYE, CHRIS.

02:02.250 --> 02:04.115
WELL, YOU HAVE
A GREAT DAY,

02:04.150 --> 02:07.051
AND MAYBE I'LL SEE YOU LATER --
OR, UH, NEVER.

02:07.090 --> 02:09.285
SEE YA. I MEAN, BYE.

02:10.360 --> 02:13.090
HEY, IT'S, UM --
I-IT'S DIAZ, RIGHT?

02:13.130 --> 02:15.325
UH, WHY?
WHAT HAVE YOU HEARD?

02:17.730 --> 02:19.869
***

02:22.540 --> 02:25.464
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

02:29.140 --> 02:31.108
YOU CAME IN EARLY.

02:31.150 --> 02:32.071
UH, YEAH,

02:32.110 --> 02:34.271
WELL, THE BALCONY PREDATOR'S
STILL OUT THERE,

02:34.320 --> 02:36.447
AND HE'S JUST GONNA GO
TO DIFFERENT NEIGHBORHOODS

02:36.490 --> 02:38.344
AND ATTACK OTHER WOMEN,
SO GOT TO FIND HIM.

02:38.390 --> 02:41.018
WELL, SEX CRIMES IS ON IT NOW,
ANDY. T-THEY'RE HANDLING IT.

02:41.060 --> 02:42.254
YEP.

02:42.290 --> 02:43.723
THEY'LL GET HIM.

02:43.760 --> 02:45.751
[ TELEPHONES RINGING ]

02:48.800 --> 02:49.869
IS THERE MILK IN THAT?

02:49.900 --> 02:51.595
YEAH. DOUBLE, DOUBLE.

02:51.630 --> 02:55.532
WELL, I TAKE THREE NOW, SO...
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

03:10.020 --> 03:12.215
Andy: HEY. [SIGHS]
ANDY.

03:12.260 --> 03:14.251
JUST WAS COMING
TO GET SOME MILK.
I TOOK THE LAST OF IT. HERE.

03:14.290 --> 03:16.429
NO, NO, NO,
THAT'S OKAY. UM...

03:16.460 --> 03:19.429
IT'S PROBABLY GOOD
FOR THE -- [ SIGHS ]

03:22.830 --> 03:23.922
THIS IS HARD.

03:24.970 --> 03:27.530
YOU KNOW, I DIDN'T EXACTLY
PLAN ON GETTING PREGNANT

03:27.570 --> 03:29.663
WITH THE GUY WHO DUMPED ME,
SO...

03:29.710 --> 03:32.270
[ SIGHS ]

03:32.310 --> 03:33.868
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL HIM BEFORE?

03:34.940 --> 03:38.307
'CAUSE I WAS GONNA
DO IT MYSELF.

03:38.350 --> 03:40.045
I APPLIED FOR A TRANSFER
OUT OF TOWN,

03:40.080 --> 03:41.411
BUT IT HASN'T COME THROUGH.

03:43.120 --> 03:45.111
LOOK, ANDY, I...

03:45.150 --> 03:46.583
I PROMISE YOU, OKAY?

03:46.620 --> 03:49.726
I AM...HERE JUST TO
DO MY JOB, ALL RIGHT?

03:49.760 --> 03:52.228
I'M NOT HERE
TO GET IN BETWEEN YOU AND SAM.

04:01.270 --> 04:02.237
HEY.
HEY.

04:02.270 --> 04:03.339
WHAT'S WRONG?

04:03.370 --> 04:05.736
I-I'M RUNNING AROUND
LIKE AN IDIOT RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

04:05.770 --> 04:07.670
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH MYSELF.

04:07.710 --> 04:09.746
WHAT'S THAT ANIMAL,
YOU KNOW, THE ONE THAT --

04:09.780 --> 04:11.099
THAT CAN'T STOP MOVING
OR IT'LL DIE?

04:11.150 --> 04:14.813
UH, A SHARK?
NO, A SHARK DOESN'T DESCRIBE
HOW I'M FEELING RIGHT NOW.

04:14.850 --> 04:16.112
A SHARK IS A FISH ANYWAY.

04:16.150 --> 04:17.686
I WISH I WAS A FISH.
YOU KNOW WHY?

04:17.720 --> 04:19.984
BECAUSE FISH FERTILIZE EGGS
OUTSIDE OF THEIR BODY.

04:20.020 --> 04:21.658
IT DOESN'T MA'I'I'ER
WHO THEY HAVE OFFSPRING WITH,

04:21.690 --> 04:23.658
BECAUSE -- BECAUSE
THEY DON'T HAVE

04:23.690 --> 04:25.988
CONFUSING EMOTIONS
LIKE RAGE AND --

04:26.030 --> 04:27.224
AND SADNESS.

04:27.260 --> 04:29.125
YOU'RE HEARTBROKEN.

04:29.160 --> 04:31.924
HEARTBROKEN?
TRACI, I'M TERRIFIED.

04:31.970 --> 04:34.188
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO DO THIS.

04:34.240 --> 04:35.696
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF I CAN DO IT.

04:35.740 --> 04:40.302
SAM'S ABOUT TO HAVE A BABY,
AND IT'S NOT WITH ME.

04:40.340 --> 04:42.137
HAVE YOU TALKED TO HIM?

04:42.180 --> 04:45.502
I CAN'T TALK TO HIM.
WHAT AM I GONNA SAY?

04:45.550 --> 04:47.472
I HAVE NO PART IN THIS.

04:47.520 --> 04:49.579
YOU DO HAVE A PART IN THIS.
WHAT?

04:49.620 --> 04:52.885
TO BE THE BIGGER PERSON?
I DON'T EVEN KNOW...

04:52.920 --> 04:58.028
WHAT THAT PERSON WOULD DO,
EXCEPT MAYBE TO...

04:58.060 --> 04:59.322
WALK AWAY.

04:59.360 --> 05:00.998
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I MEAN...

05:01.030 --> 05:02.793
[ SIGHS ]

05:02.830 --> 05:05.424
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE SAM SHOULD BE WITH MARLO.

05:05.470 --> 05:07.495
TRACI, THERE'S A FAMILY
AT RECEPTION

05:07.540 --> 05:09.963
LOOKING TO FILE
A MISSING-PERSONS REPORT.

05:10.010 --> 05:11.534
UH, WHO'S MISSING?

05:11.570 --> 05:13.470
THEIR 16-YEAR-OLD
DAUGHTER.

05:13.510 --> 05:16.138
OKAY, WE ARE NOT DONE
THIS CONVERSATION.

05:16.180 --> 05:18.375
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

05:19.550 --> 05:21.916
OH, HEY.
I'M OFFICER NICK COLLINS.

05:21.950 --> 05:23.588
STOP IT.

05:23.620 --> 05:26.453
WHAT? I'M JUST GOING WITH IT.
WE DON'T KNOW EACH OTHER, RIGHT?

05:26.490 --> 05:30.984
WELL, WE DON'T...REALLY
KNOW EACH OTHER, SO --

05:31.030 --> 05:32.088
Nick:
OKAY. IT'S YOUR LOSS.

05:32.130 --> 05:35.293
I'M KIND OF KNOWN AS
A PERSON OF WISDOM AROUND HERE.

05:35.330 --> 05:36.922
"A PERSON OF WISDOM"?

05:36.970 --> 05:37.891
YEP.
MM.

05:37.930 --> 05:40.194
I'M SURE YOU'LL DO FINE
WITHOUT MY INSIGHT.

05:40.240 --> 05:41.935
[ SCOFFS ]

05:41.970 --> 05:42.902
OH!

05:42.940 --> 05:44.601
WHAT?

05:45.440 --> 05:46.600
IT'S NOTHING.

05:46.640 --> 05:47.868
WHAT?

05:47.910 --> 05:49.673
THAT'S THE BAD-LUCK RADIO.

05:49.710 --> 05:52.042
THERE'S A BAD-LUCK RADIO?
IT'S CURSED.

05:52.080 --> 05:53.718
MM-HMM,
AND HOW IS IT CURSED?

05:53.750 --> 05:56.446
IT'S MORE OF
AN "OVER BEERS" STORY.

05:56.490 --> 05:57.809
UM, YEAH, NO BEERS.

05:57.850 --> 05:59.454
I AGREE.
WE SHOULD KEEP OUR DISTANCE.

05:59.490 --> 06:01.981
[ CLEARS THROAT ] MAINTAIN
A PROFESSIONAL RELATIONSHIP.

06:02.020 --> 06:03.487
GOT IT.
GOOD.

06:03.530 --> 06:07.193
HEY, COLLINS. YOU'RE GONNA
BE RIDING WITH WARD TODAY, OKAY?

06:07.230 --> 06:09.425
GREAT.

06:20.010 --> 06:22.308
WHAT TIME DID YOU LAST
SEE YOUR DAUGHTER?

06:22.340 --> 06:23.443
PLEASE, HAVE A SEAT.

06:23.480 --> 06:27.519
UH, 7:30 LAST NIGHT. ELLEN
SENT HER DOWN TO MONROE'S GAS

06:27.550 --> 06:28.915
AT THE CORNER
OF QUEEN AND JAMESON.

06:28.950 --> 06:30.486
IT'S JUST A BLOCK
FROM OUR HOUSE.

06:30.520 --> 06:33.648
Ellen:
I NEEDED MILK FOR THE MORNING.

06:33.690 --> 06:35.089
I'D BEEN
AND GOTI'EN GROCERIES ALREADY,

06:35.120 --> 06:37.429
BUT I FORGOT THE MILK,
WHICH IS WHAT I WENT FOR.

06:38.390 --> 06:41.188
9:00 P.M., I-I-I WENT
DOWN TO THE GAS STATION

06:41.230 --> 06:46.065
TO LOOK FOR HER. IT WAS CLOSED,
SO I-I-I WENT HOME.

06:46.100 --> 06:47.863
I GOT IN MY CAR,
AND I JUST...

06:47.900 --> 06:50.334
I DROVE AROUND.
I WAS LOOKING FOR HER ALL NIGHT.

06:50.370 --> 06:52.474
YOU'VE OBVIOUSLY
TRIED HER CELLPHONE?

06:52.510 --> 06:54.671
HAYLEY DOESN'T HAVE
A CELLPHONE.

06:54.710 --> 06:56.541
SHE LIVES AT HOME.
WE HAVE A PHONE.

06:56.580 --> 06:58.605
OKAY. HAS SHE STAYED OUT
ALL NIGHT BEFORE?

06:58.650 --> 07:00.709
WHEN I WAS 16,
I WAS STAYING

07:00.750 --> 07:02.513
AT MY FRIEND'S HOUSE
ALL THE TIME.

07:02.550 --> 07:03.949
SHE DOESN'T HAVE
ANY FRIENDS.

07:05.090 --> 07:08.150
WE ONLY MOVED TO THE CITY
A YEAR AGO, AND MY -- MY WIFE

07:08.190 --> 07:11.921
HAS FATIGUE ISSUES, SO HAYLEY
HELPS OUT A LOT AFTER SCHOOL.

07:11.960 --> 07:14.190
WHAT WAS YOUR DAUGHTER WEARING
THE LAST TIME YOU SAW HER?

07:14.230 --> 07:16.357
UM...

07:16.400 --> 07:18.425
JEANS.

07:18.470 --> 07:20.165
RUNNING SHOES.
[ SIGHS ]

07:20.200 --> 07:24.466
THE -- THE PINK T-SHIRT,
THE ONE WITH THE UNICORN ON IT.

07:24.510 --> 07:25.602
SHE STILL HAS THAT SHIRT?

07:25.640 --> 07:27.437
I THOUGHT
SHE GOT RID OF THAT SHIRT.

07:27.480 --> 07:29.334
SHE WAS JUST GOING TO WEAR IT
AROUND THE HOUSE.

07:29.380 --> 07:31.143
EXCEPT SHE WORE IT
LAST NIGHT.

07:33.150 --> 07:34.845
IT'S NOT
AN APPROPRIATE SHIRT.

07:37.350 --> 07:38.908
GAS STATION
ALWAYS CLOSE AT 9:00?

07:38.950 --> 07:41.316
[ INHALES SLOWLY ]

07:41.360 --> 07:42.349
I DON'T KNOW.

07:42.390 --> 07:44.187
I'M GONNA
GIVE THEM A CALL.

07:45.990 --> 07:46.991
[ SIGHS ]

07:47.030 --> 07:48.327
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

07:48.360 --> 07:49.725
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

07:49.770 --> 07:51.692
ANDY,
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

07:51.730 --> 07:53.891
GAS-STATION MANAGER
SAID THAT THIS EMPLOYEE

07:53.940 --> 07:57.068
CLOSED EARLY LAST NIGHT AND
DID NOT SHOW UP THIS MORNING.

07:57.110 --> 07:58.361
YEAH?
CONNOR FRYE, 21.

07:58.410 --> 08:00.378
OKAY, WERE THERE
SECURITY CAMERAS?

08:00.410 --> 08:01.729
NO, BUT HE HAS A RECORD --

08:01.780 --> 08:04.499
UH, CAR THEl-T
AND A COUPLE MINOR B&ES.

08:04.550 --> 08:05.403
THAT'S IT?

08:05.450 --> 08:08.317
THIS IS CONNOR FRYE'S
JUVENILE RECORD.

08:08.350 --> 08:09.476
IT WAS EXPUNGED.

08:09.520 --> 08:11.613
SO, WHAT,
YOU UN-EXPUNGED IT?

08:11.650 --> 08:13.186
OKAY.
WHEN HE WAS 14,

08:13.220 --> 08:16.781
HE COERCED AN 11-YEAR-OLD GIRL
INTO SEXUAL ACTIVITY.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.856
I FOUND THESE ON CONNOR FRYE'S
INSTAGRAM PHOTO STREAM.

08:19.900 --> 08:21.959
SUBJECT FOR THIS
WAS "THIS BEAUTY."

08:22.000 --> 08:25.697
NOW, I DON'T THINK SHE KNEW THAT
THESE PHOTOS WERE BEING TAKEN.

08:25.730 --> 08:29.336
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S FIND HAYLEY HILL.

08:29.370 --> 08:30.564
THANK YOU.

08:30.610 --> 08:32.578
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

08:32.610 --> 08:34.805
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:36.610 --> 08:38.146
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

08:38.180 --> 08:40.819
OH, HEY.
LET ME GET THAT.

08:40.850 --> 08:43.944
I APPRECIATE
YOUR CHIVALRY.

08:43.990 --> 08:46.857
[ Quietly ] DON'T WORRY.
THEY'RE STARING AT ME, TOO.

08:46.890 --> 08:48.653
I SERIOUSLY DOUBT THAT,
DOV.

08:48.690 --> 08:51.284
MY EX-GIRLFRIEND MADE OUT
WITH HER EX-HUSBAND,

08:51.330 --> 08:53.150
WHO WAS ACTUALLY
STILL HER HUSBAND,

08:53.200 --> 08:56.522
BEFORE SHE WAS MY EX-GIRLFRIEND.
THE POINT IS, PEOPLE TALK.

08:56.570 --> 08:57.923
SCREW 'EM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:57.970 --> 09:00.632
SO, WHO'S THIS UPSTANDING
CITIZEN?

09:00.670 --> 09:02.638
[ SIGHS ] THAT GUY,
ALONG WITH THE REST

09:02.670 --> 09:04.968
OF THE PIMPS, PROSTITUTES,
AND DEALERS IN THIS BOX,

09:05.010 --> 09:07.638
WERE ALL ARRESTED ON THE DAY
OUR EVIDENCE ROOM BLEW UP.

09:07.680 --> 09:09.477
AND THEY ALL HAD
EVIDENCE LOGGED IN,

09:09.510 --> 09:11.444
SO WE'RE GONNA TRY
TO FIND A CONNECTION.

09:11.480 --> 09:12.947
CONNECTION TO WHO --
TED MCDONALD?

09:12.980 --> 09:15.448
NOPE. [ SIGHS ]
CONNECTION TO THE BOMB ITSELF.

09:15.480 --> 09:17.448
WE'RE GOING BACK
TO FIRST PRINCIPLES.

09:17.490 --> 09:18.787
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

09:18.820 --> 09:21.584
SO WE'RE GONNA TRY TO CONNECT
ONE OF THESE GUYS

09:21.620 --> 09:23.326
TO A COMPONENT FROM THE BOMB.

09:23.360 --> 09:24.952
[ SIGHS ]
WORKING THEORY --

09:24.990 --> 09:27.993
IF YOU WANT TO GET SOMETHING
INTO THE EVIDENCE ROOM...

09:28.030 --> 09:31.022
...HAVE IT ON YOU
WHEN YOU GET ARRESTED.

09:35.040 --> 09:36.928
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE CONNOR WAS LAST NIGHT.

09:36.970 --> 09:39.336
HE WASN'T HERE
WHEN I GOT HOME.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.577
BUT HIS --
HIS CAMPER WAS GONE.

09:41.610 --> 09:44.170
IS THAT UNUSUAL?
NO, HE GOES FOR DAYS.

09:44.210 --> 09:50.285
HE LIKES THE OPEN ROAD...
JUST LIKE HIS DEADBEAT FATHER.

09:50.320 --> 09:51.446
ALL RIGHT, LET'S, UH...

09:51.490 --> 09:54.186
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

09:56.520 --> 09:58.727
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:01.860 --> 10:03.293
THAT'S HIS TARANTULA.

10:05.830 --> 10:06.933
W-WHERE --
WHERE IS IT?

10:06.970 --> 10:10.667
LOOK, I KNOW I'M SUPPOSED
TO TELL YOU HE'S A GOOD BOY.

10:10.710 --> 10:12.359
BUT HE'S NOT.

10:12.410 --> 10:15.106
MAYBE JAIL WOULD STRAIGHTEN
HIM OUT. GOD KNOWS I CAN'T.

10:15.140 --> 10:18.906
YOU THINK IT GOT OUT, OR HE --
HE JUST TOOK IT WITH HIM?

10:18.950 --> 10:21.544
I DON'T SEE --
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

10:21.580 --> 10:23.582
I FELT IT. THAT WAS IT.
I'M SORRY. EXCUSE ME.

10:23.620 --> 10:25.679
THAT'S IT. THAT WAS IT.
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

10:25.720 --> 10:27.187
I FELT SOMETHING
ON THE BACK OF MY NECK.

10:27.220 --> 10:28.983
THINK WE NEED TO
DO OUR JOB RIGHT NOW,

10:29.020 --> 10:30.920
SO YOU NEED TO LOCK IT UP.
IT'S NOT IN THERE.

10:30.960 --> 10:34.418
SORRY. UM, WHERE WAS
THIS PHOTO TAKEN?

10:34.460 --> 10:35.996
A CAMPGROUND
HE USED TO GO TO

10:36.030 --> 10:38.419
WHEN HIS FATHER WAS AROUND --
HINKS BAY.

10:38.470 --> 10:40.392
HINKS BAY.

10:40.440 --> 10:42.192
HINKS BAY --
I-IT'S THE OFF-SEASON.

10:42.240 --> 10:43.161
SO IT'S PROBABLY EMPTY.

10:43.210 --> 10:45.667
YES, LET'S CALL IT IN.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

10:45.710 --> 10:46.608
1504.
1504.

10:46.640 --> 10:48.278
OKAY.

10:48.310 --> 10:49.846
15--
15--

10:50.650 --> 10:52.379
[ BIRD CALLS ]

10:54.520 --> 10:56.374
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:58.750 --> 11:01.116
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

11:02.930 --> 11:05.387
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

11:10.800 --> 11:13.166
CONNOR FRYE?

11:13.200 --> 11:14.394
WHERE'S HAYLEY, HMM?

11:14.440 --> 11:16.192
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

11:16.240 --> 11:18.663
YOU'RE WANTED FOR QUESTIONING
IN HER DISAPPEARANCE.

11:18.710 --> 11:19.734
I DON'T KNOW WHO THAT IS.

11:19.780 --> 11:22.101
WE SAW THE PHOTOS. WE KNOW
THAT YOU'RE STALKING HER.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.301
I'M PRETTY SURE YOU KNOW
WHO WE'RE TALKING ABOUT.

11:24.350 --> 11:26.602
SO WHY DON'T YOU
SAVE US SOME TIME, CONNOR,

11:26.650 --> 11:27.969
AND TELL US WHERE SHE IS?

11:28.020 --> 11:29.214
HEY!

11:30.890 --> 11:33.188
HE'S GOT A POLICE SCANNER.
KNEW WE WERE COMING.

11:33.220 --> 11:34.756
WHERE IS SHE?!

11:34.790 --> 11:37.122
THERE'S NOBODY HERE
EXCEPT ME.

11:42.630 --> 11:44.461
DIAZ, MAKE ME A CUP.

11:44.500 --> 11:46.388
JARVIS IS LOOKING FOR YOU.

11:46.430 --> 11:49.092
ME? JARVIS?
F-FOR WHAT?

11:49.140 --> 11:51.233
YOU KNOW, MY JOB
IS NOT TO QUESTION HIM,

11:51.270 --> 11:53.170
AND YOUR JOB IS
NOT TO QUESTION ME.

11:53.210 --> 11:55.178
HE'S IN THE PARADE ROOM.
THANK YOU.

11:55.210 --> 11:56.472
DOV.

11:56.510 --> 11:58.171
HEY.

11:59.110 --> 12:02.045
HEY, DOV, THE CAMERAS
IN THE PARKING LOT --

12:02.080 --> 12:03.889
THEY'RE JUST POINTED
AT THE EXITS, RIGHT?

12:03.920 --> 12:05.842
NAH, I'M PRETTY SURE
THEY COVER THE WHOLE LOT.

12:15.800 --> 12:16.767
INSPECTOR.

12:16.800 --> 12:19.098
I KNOW ABOUT YOU, DIAZ.

12:20.300 --> 12:24.031
YOUR FILE SAYS YOU WORKED
CONSTRUCTION BEFORE THE ACADEMY?

12:24.070 --> 12:25.901
YEAH. YEAH,
FOR A COUPLE OF YEARS.

12:25.940 --> 12:28.909
OKAY, SO, LET ME
GIVE YOU A HYPOTHETICAL.

12:28.940 --> 12:31.602
LET'S SAY MY OFFICE,
ALTHOUGH STATELY, IS...

12:31.650 --> 12:32.674
SLIGHTLY COZY.

12:32.710 --> 12:35.440
AND LET'S SAY THAT
THE EMPTY OFFICE NEXT TO MINE

12:35.480 --> 12:38.688
WILL, IN TWO WEEKS, BE HOME
TO A NEW LIAISON OFFICER,

12:38.720 --> 12:40.256
AN OFFICER
WHO HAS NO IDEA

12:40.290 --> 12:42.679
HOW BIG THAT OFFICE
IS SUPPOSED TO BE.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.756
DIAZ,
YOU CATCHING MY DRIl-T?

12:46.030 --> 12:49.295
[ SIGHS ]
T-TOTALLY. YEP.

12:50.470 --> 12:53.564
I WOULD LIKE TO
APPROPRIATE...

12:53.600 --> 12:56.569
2 FEET
OF THE OFFICE NEXT TO MINE.

12:56.600 --> 12:58.864
NOW, 2 FEET IS NEGLIGIBLE.
ARE YOU...

12:58.910 --> 13:01.731
COMFORTABLE...
WITH THAT, SIR?

13:01.780 --> 13:02.974
[ SCOFFS ]
HE'LL HAVE NO IDEA.

13:03.010 --> 13:04.773
I DON'T SEE
HOW IT'LL AFFECT HIM.

13:06.150 --> 13:08.539
I'M HEADED DOWNTOWN
FOR A BUDGET MEETING.

13:08.580 --> 13:11.083
HAVE A LOOK.

13:11.120 --> 13:13.259
WE'LL TALK
WHEN I GET BACK.

13:13.290 --> 13:14.211
YES, SIR.

13:14.260 --> 13:18.082
AND, DIAZ, I'D LIKE
TO KEEP THIS BETWEEN US.

13:21.400 --> 13:22.890
[ BUZZER SOUNDS ]

13:22.930 --> 13:24.727
WHERE'S THE GIRL,
CONNOR?

13:24.770 --> 13:26.294
I DON'T KNOW THAT GIRL.

13:28.640 --> 13:30.130
TAKE A SEAT.

13:32.740 --> 13:34.503
THEN WHAT ARE THESE?

13:34.540 --> 13:37.145
TAKE A LOT OF PHOTOS.
I DON'T ALWAYS ASK PERMISSION.

13:37.180 --> 13:38.943
SO IT'S A COINCIDENCE
YOU'VE BEEN

13:38.980 --> 13:41.642
OBSESSIVELY TAKING PHOTOS
OF A GIRL WHO'S DISAPPEARED?

13:41.680 --> 13:43.386
I GUESS SO.

13:43.420 --> 13:46.048
SHE'S VERY PRETTY.
DO YOU THINK SHE'S PRETTY?

13:47.190 --> 13:48.316
I DON'T KNOW.

13:48.360 --> 13:50.624
OH, COME ON.
YOU DON'T KNOW
IF YOU THINK SHE'S PRETTY?

13:50.660 --> 13:52.457
OKAY, SHE'S PRETTY.
IS SHE NICE?

13:55.200 --> 13:57.020
LOOK AT HER FACE.
IS THAT A NICE FACE?

13:58.470 --> 13:59.596
I GUESS.

13:59.630 --> 14:02.098
SO YOU WOULDN'T WANT ANYTHING
TO HAPPEN TO HER, WOULD YOU?

14:02.140 --> 14:04.028
IF IT DID,
IT WOULDN'T BE MY FAULT.

14:05.640 --> 14:07.835
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:10.380 --> 14:13.042
WE HAVE A SUSPECT IN CUSTODY.
HE WORKS AT THE GAS STATION.

14:13.080 --> 14:14.945
DOES HE HAVE HAYLEY?

14:14.980 --> 14:17.039
UH, WE HAVEN'T FOUND HER YET,
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE

14:17.090 --> 14:19.513
THAT HE'S BEEN FOLLOWING HER
FOR QUITE SOME TIME NOW.

14:19.550 --> 14:20.881
DO YOU GUYS RECOGNIZE HIM?

14:21.720 --> 14:23.551
I KNOW WHO THAT IS.

14:23.590 --> 14:26.320
HE STARES AT HER
EVERY TIME WE GO IN THERE.
YOU KNOW HIM?

14:26.360 --> 14:29.193
HE JUST STARES.
HAS HE EVER SPOKEN TO HAYLEY?

14:29.230 --> 14:30.925
YOU PUT ME IN A ROOM WITH HIM,
AND I'LL FIND OUT.

14:30.970 --> 14:34.633
MR. HILL, UM...
IS IT POSSIBLE

14:34.670 --> 14:37.537
THAT MAYBE HE KNOWS HER
BETTER THAN YOU THINK HE DOES?

14:37.570 --> 14:38.798
NO, ABSOLUTELY NOT.

14:38.840 --> 14:40.478
OH, DEAR GOD.
[ SIGHS ]

14:40.510 --> 14:43.707
ELLEN, STOP THAT.
IF YOU NEED TO PRAY, JUST PRAY.

14:43.750 --> 14:44.500
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

14:44.550 --> 14:46.404
WE'RE GONNA
FIND YOUR DAUGHTER.

14:48.120 --> 14:50.315
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

15:00.530 --> 15:02.555
[ DOG PANTING ]

15:06.530 --> 15:10.466
HEY, THE CAMPER'S PRETTY CLEAN.
THERE'S NO SIGN OF HER.

15:10.510 --> 15:12.501
WAIT A MINUTE.
THERE'S SOMETHING HERE.

15:17.410 --> 15:18.479
[ SIGHS ]

15:18.510 --> 15:21.274
SHE WAS WEARING A PINK TANK TOP
WHEN SHE WENT MISSING.

15:25.620 --> 15:29.249
HE SAID IF SOMETHING HAPPENED TO
HER, IT WOULDN'T BE HIS FAULT.

15:29.290 --> 15:31.827
WHOSE FAULT WOULD IT BE?
GOT A THEORY?

15:31.860 --> 15:33.828
YEAH, MAYBE HE'S NOT
THE ONLY ONE INVOLVED.

15:33.860 --> 15:35.725
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
THE NEW GIRL CALLED AND SAID

15:35.760 --> 15:38.661
SHE FOUND HAYLEY'S TANK TOP IN
THE FIRE PIT OF THE CAMPGROUND.

15:38.700 --> 15:41.567
THEORY?
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

15:42.370 --> 15:43.462
[ DOOR BEEPS ]

15:43.510 --> 15:47.970
OKAY, SO, WE FOUND HAYLEY'S
SHIRT OUTSIDE YOUR CAMPER.

15:48.010 --> 15:49.932
THAT'S GONNA MATTER
IN SENTENCING.

15:49.980 --> 15:52.278
SENTENCING FOR WHAT?
FIRST-DEGREE MURDER.

15:52.310 --> 15:54.369
[ SCOFFS ] YOU CAN'T CHARGE ME
WITH MURDER. THERE'S NO BODY.

15:54.420 --> 15:57.309
WE DON'T NEED A BODY
TO CHARGE YOU WITH MURDER!

15:57.350 --> 15:59.818
I SAVED HER.

15:59.850 --> 16:01.056
YOU SAVED HER?

16:01.090 --> 16:03.126
SHE COULDN'T
LIVE LIKE THAT ANYMORE.

16:03.160 --> 16:04.388
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

16:04.430 --> 16:05.488
THIS WASN'T MY IDEA.

16:05.530 --> 16:08.727
CONNOR! YOU NEED TO TELL US
WHAT'S GOING ON RIGHT NOW!

16:12.730 --> 16:14.197
[ GRUNTS,
BREATH ES HEAVILY ]

16:14.240 --> 16:16.834
YOU'RE GETTING A TRANSFER
TO MILLBURN PENITENTIARY,

16:16.870 --> 16:17.939
AND WHILE YOU'RE IN THERE

16:17.970 --> 16:20.632
WAITING FOR YOUR CRAPPY,
PRO BONO LAWYER TO TURN UP...

16:20.680 --> 16:24.446
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK ]
...I'M GONNA MAKE SURE EVERYBODY
KNOWS WHAT YOU'RE IN FOR...

16:24.480 --> 16:28.041
...KIDNAPPING, CHILD MOLESTING,
POSSIBLE HOMICIDE.

16:28.080 --> 16:30.219
I CAN'T IMAGINE
YOU'LL STILL BE IN ONE PIECE

16:30.250 --> 16:32.081
BY THE TIME
YOUR LAWYER GETS THERE.

16:32.120 --> 16:34.418
COME ON.
OKAY, I'LL TELL YOU,
I'LL TELL YOU.

16:34.460 --> 16:36.212
I'LL TAKE YOU TO HER.
[ SIGHS ]

16:36.260 --> 16:37.522
I'LL TAKE YOU TO HER.

16:39.060 --> 16:40.493
Marlo:
SO, I MADE US A SNACK,

16:40.530 --> 16:42.953
AND THEN I ATE HALF OF IT
ON THE WAY BACK HERE.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.422
[ Muffled ]
WHAT HAVE WE GOT?

16:44.470 --> 16:46.324
WELL, I'D SAY
BETWEEN THE TWO OF US,

16:46.370 --> 16:48.463
WE GOT ABOUT A HALF A SNACK,
AND THAT'S IT.

16:48.500 --> 16:50.229
[ CHUCKLES ]
WALK ME THROUGH IT.

16:50.270 --> 16:52.033
ALL RIGHT,
THE EVIDENCE-ROOM BOMB

16:52.070 --> 16:54.129
WAS MADE WITH
INDUSTRIAL-GRADE EXPLOSIVES.

16:54.180 --> 16:55.704
NOW, YOU NEED A LICENSE
TO BUY THOSE.

16:55.740 --> 16:58.049
THE COMPANY THAT MAKES THEM,
FRACK MANUFACTURING,

16:58.080 --> 16:59.570
IS LOCKED UP
TIGHTER THAN FORT KNOX.

16:59.610 --> 17:02.340
OKAY, SO OUR BOMBER
DIDN'T STEAL THEM.

17:02.380 --> 17:03.608
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.
FRACK HASN'T REPORTED A THEl-T,

17:03.650 --> 17:07.086
AND WE'RE NOT EXACTLY DEALING
WITH THE BEST AND THE BRIGHTEST,

17:07.120 --> 17:08.280
EVEN AS FAR AS CRIMINALS GO.

17:08.320 --> 17:11.357
NOW, HERE IS A LIST OF EVERYONE
WHO WAS ARRESTED THAT DAY.

17:11.390 --> 17:13.358
THIS IS A LIST
OF ALL FRACK EMPLOYEES

17:13.400 --> 17:15.220
AND EVERYONE
WHO BUYS FROM FRACK.

17:15.260 --> 17:20.368
OKAY, SO, EITHER TED MCDONALD
OR ONE OF THESE OTHER CRIMINALS

17:20.400 --> 17:23.699
ILLEGALLY PURCHASED
EXPLOSIVES FROM...

17:23.740 --> 17:26.561
ONE OF THESE NAMES.

17:26.610 --> 17:27.679
LET'S CONNECT THEM.

17:27.710 --> 17:30.599
LET'S SEE.
MARY CHANG WENT TO BOOK CLUB,

17:30.650 --> 17:34.177
AND WHAT DO YOU KNOW?
SO DID ALDO "ICEPICK" PEREZ.

17:34.220 --> 17:35.915
YES, EXCEPT
IT'S PROBABLY NOT BOOK CLUB.

17:35.950 --> 17:40.387
IT'S PROBABLY, A-A DEEP, DARK
WEB FORUM ABOUT BOMB MAKING.

17:40.420 --> 17:43.628
OKAY. SO,
WE'RE GONNA LOOK

17:43.660 --> 17:48.654
FROM JUVIE TO BABYSITTING CLASS
AND EVERYWHERE IN BETWEEN.

17:48.700 --> 17:51.168
WE'RE GONNA NEED
A BIGGER SNACK.
MM-HMM.

17:51.200 --> 17:53.794
[ SIREN CHIRPS ]

17:53.840 --> 17:56.229
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

17:56.270 --> 17:58.465
WHAT ARE WE GONNA FIND,
CONNOR?

18:04.380 --> 18:06.473
Andy:
HEY, WE'RE READY TO GO.

18:15.890 --> 18:18.085
DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

18:21.830 --> 18:23.491
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

18:27.270 --> 18:29.864
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER
CONTINUES ]

18:34.310 --> 18:36.369
SHE'S SOMEWHERE AROUND HERE.

18:39.450 --> 18:40.439
THERE.

18:41.850 --> 18:43.647
NASH?
YEAH, YEAH.

18:43.690 --> 18:45.317
[ DOG BARKING ]

18:46.290 --> 18:47.951
Sam:
GET THIS DOG OUT OF HERE!

18:47.990 --> 18:49.287
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!
SAM!

18:49.320 --> 18:51.129
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

18:54.260 --> 18:56.820
[ GRUNTING ]
GET OFF ME!

18:56.860 --> 18:59.294
[ GRUNTS ]
I SAID GET OFF ME!

18:59.330 --> 19:01.469
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
HAYLEY HILL.

19:06.440 --> 19:08.328
HAYLEY, YOUR PARENTS
ARE REALLY WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

19:08.380 --> 19:09.608
MY PARENTS
ARE NOT WORRIED ABOUT ME.

19:09.640 --> 19:13.041
THEY ARE WORRIED
ABOUT MY SOUL.
SO, CONNOR DIDN'T HURT YOU?

19:13.080 --> 19:14.638
OF COURSE NOT.

19:14.680 --> 19:17.911
NOW, CAN YOU PLEASE UNCUFF HIM
SO THAT WE CAN GET OUT OF HERE?

19:17.950 --> 19:18.689
[ DOG BARKING ]

19:18.720 --> 19:20.381
I'M GONNA GO
CALL YOUR PARENTS.

19:20.420 --> 19:21.819
GET THAT DOG OUT OF HERE.

19:21.860 --> 19:22.758
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

19:22.790 --> 19:24.883
COULD'VE SAVED YOURSELF
A LOT OF TROUBLE

19:24.930 --> 19:26.386
IF YOU HAD JUST
TOLD THE TRUTH.

19:26.430 --> 19:27.454
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

19:27.500 --> 19:29.752
WE THOUGHT YOU'D LET ME GO
WHEN YOU FIGURED THAT OUT.

19:29.800 --> 19:30.698
BUT YOU DIDN'T.

19:30.730 --> 19:33.096
SO, THE PLAN WAS JUST
TO RUN AWAY TOGETHER?

19:33.130 --> 19:34.893
IS THAT IT?

19:34.940 --> 19:36.532
MY PARENTS ARE INSANE.

19:36.570 --> 19:39.437
I'M NOT ALLOWED TO GO TO DANCES.
I CAN'T WALK TO THE STORE.

19:39.470 --> 19:40.971
I CAN'T WEAR MY OWN SHIRTS.

19:41.010 --> 19:42.329
TELL THEM ABOUT
THE OTHER STUFF.

19:42.380 --> 19:45.304
WHAT OTHER STUFF?

19:46.410 --> 19:50.119
HER DAD FED HER DOG POISON,
MADE HER WATCH IT DIE.

19:50.150 --> 19:52.289
THEN THREW IT OUT OF THE CAR
ON NEWMAN'S LINE.

19:52.320 --> 19:53.139
UH, HAYLEY, IS THAT TRUE?

19:53.190 --> 19:55.909
PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME
GO BACK WITH THEM.

19:55.960 --> 19:57.985
LEGALLY,
THEY HAVE CUSTODY OF YOU.

19:58.030 --> 19:59.281
YOU'RE ONLY 16 YEARS OLD.

19:59.330 --> 20:02.629
WHEN SHE ASKED HER DAD IF SHE
COULD GO TO A MOVIE WITH A GUY,

20:02.660 --> 20:05.322
HE MADE HER SLEEP
IN THE GARAGE OVERNIGHT.

20:05.370 --> 20:06.621
IS THAT ILLEGAL?

20:06.670 --> 20:09.559
NO. NOT REALLY.

20:09.600 --> 20:11.761
HE MAKES ME STAY UP ALL NIGHT
TO DO MY HOMEWORK,

20:11.810 --> 20:16.031
AND IF I GET IT WRONG,
THEN HE WHIPS OUT HIS BELT.

20:16.080 --> 20:17.604
WHAT ABOUT THAT?

20:17.650 --> 20:18.969
IS THAT ILLEGAL?

20:19.010 --> 20:20.272
ARE YOU SAYING
HE ABUSES YOU?

20:20.320 --> 20:22.641
L-LOOK, I...

20:22.680 --> 20:25.387
I DON'T WANT HIM
TO GO TO JAIL, OKAY? I JUST --

20:25.420 --> 20:28.856
[ SIGHS ]
I JUST WANT TO BE WITH CONNOR.

20:28.890 --> 20:30.824
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

20:35.160 --> 20:36.991
HAVE YOU FOUND HER?
YES. SHE'S SAFE.

20:37.030 --> 20:38.588
DID THAT BOY
LAY HIS HANDS ON HER?

20:38.630 --> 20:41.963
YOUR DAUGHTER'S JUST FINE, SIR.
SHE'S FINE.

20:42.000 --> 20:44.161
MR. HILL,
DO YOU HAVE A DOG?

20:44.210 --> 20:46.565
OUR DOG RAN AWAY
A FEW DAYS AGO.

20:46.610 --> 20:49.272
MM.
SO HE WASN'T POISONED?

20:49.310 --> 20:51.073
DID HAYLEY TELL YOU THAT?

20:51.110 --> 20:52.179
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

20:52.210 --> 20:53.746
Sam:
MR. HILL, IS IT POSSIBLE

20:53.780 --> 20:56.317
YOUR DAUGHTER'S GOING THROUGH
A REBELLIOUS PHASE RIGHT NOW?

20:57.720 --> 21:00.143
ARE YOU SUGGESTING
MY DAUGHTER LEI-T THE HOUSE

21:00.190 --> 21:02.488
AND VOLUNTARILY SPENT THE NIGHT
WITH THAT BOY?

21:02.520 --> 21:04.886
IT'S NOT UNUSUAL
FOR A 16-YEAR-OLD GIRL.

21:04.930 --> 21:06.386
WHAT HAPPENED, DAD?

21:06.430 --> 21:07.829
IT'S OKAY, JEREMY.

21:07.860 --> 21:11.296
WHAT WILL IT TAKE TO BREAK
THAT SPITEFUL WILL OF HERS?

21:11.330 --> 21:13.730
I'M SORRY?
BREAK HER WILL?

21:16.040 --> 21:18.565
THIS IS A PRIVATE
FAMILY MATTER.

21:18.610 --> 21:20.305
I'D LIKE TO SEE
MY DAUGHTER NOW.

21:20.340 --> 21:23.901
DETECTIVE NASH IS GONNA BE
BRINGING HER HOME VERY SOON.

21:23.950 --> 21:26.601
I JUST HAVE A COUPLE OF QUICK
QUESTIONS FOR YOU, MR. HILL.

21:26.650 --> 21:29.073
YOUR FAMILY CAN STAY
AND WAIT FOR YOU IF YOU LIKE.

21:29.120 --> 21:33.147
OR I CAN TAKE THEM HOME WHERE
THEY'LL BE MORE COMFORTABLE.

21:33.190 --> 21:34.817
GO HOME, ELLEN.

21:34.860 --> 21:37.556
I WANT SOMEONE THERE
WHEN HAYLEY GETS BACK.
COME ON, JEREMY.

21:37.590 --> 21:40.024
I WANT TO STAY WITH DAD.
LISTEN TO YOUR MOTHER.

21:46.930 --> 21:48.830
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

21:48.870 --> 21:51.532
I APOLOGIZE FOR ALL THE TROUBLE
WE'VE CAUSED YOU.

21:51.570 --> 21:53.731
NO.
WHEN WILL WE GET HAYLEY HOME?

21:53.780 --> 21:56.271
UH, SHE'S JUST GONNA GIVE HER
STATEMENT TO THE DETECTIVE,

21:56.310 --> 21:58.039
AND THEN WE'RE GONNA
CLOSE THE BOOKS ON THIS.

21:58.080 --> 22:00.241
HE'S GONNA TAKE HER
TO THE GARAGE.
JEREMY...

22:00.280 --> 22:02.111
WHAT HAPPENS
IN THE GARAGE, JEREMY?

22:02.150 --> 22:03.788
DISCIPLINE
IS LLOYD'S DOMAIN.

22:05.590 --> 22:07.114
SO YOU'RE NOT PARTY
TO DISCIPLINE?

22:07.150 --> 22:09.118
WE'RE A TRADITIONAL FAMILY.

22:09.160 --> 22:10.787
I KNOW WHAT PEOPLE THINK
OF THAT.

22:10.830 --> 22:13.594
BUT IT ACTUALLY TAKES
AN INCREDIBLE AMOUNT OF STRENGTH

22:13.630 --> 22:15.928
TO SUBMIT TO YOUR HUSBAND
IN ALL THINGS.

22:15.960 --> 22:17.791
I'M SURE IT DOES.

22:28.240 --> 22:30.447
[ CHILDREN SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE ]

22:32.980 --> 22:34.470
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

22:34.520 --> 22:35.942
SO, WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO HAYLEY?

22:35.980 --> 22:38.619
HEY, I THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA
FOR YOU TO STEER CLEAR OF HAYLEY

22:38.650 --> 22:40.811
AND HER FAMILY FOR A WHILE.
THEY GOT A LOT GOING ON.

22:40.860 --> 22:42.589
SO, WHAT -- JUST GIVE UP?
I LOVE HER.

22:42.620 --> 22:44.884
WELL, MAYBE IT'S A
RIGHT GIRL/WRONG TIME SCENARIO.

22:44.930 --> 22:47.251
DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL MAKE SURE SHE'S OKAY.

22:47.290 --> 22:51.829
I'LL MAKE SURE SHE'S OKAY.
THANKS FOR THE RIDE, GUYS.

22:53.640 --> 22:55.733
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE
HE'S GONNA GIVE UP.

22:55.770 --> 22:58.204
WELL, HE DOESN'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHOICE.

22:58.240 --> 23:01.107
I'LL CALL STAFF, TELL HIM
WE'LL STICK AROUND FOR A WHILE

23:01.140 --> 23:02.607
AND MAKE SURE
THE KID STAYS PUT.

23:02.640 --> 23:03.971
[ DOOR SHUTS ]
OKAY.

23:07.550 --> 23:10.212
LLOYD, UM,
I GOT TO TELL YOU,

23:10.250 --> 23:13.287
WE HAVE TO INVESTIGATE
ABUSE CLAIMS

23:13.320 --> 23:15.185
EVEN IF THEY'RE
COMPLETELY UNFOUNDED.

23:15.220 --> 23:18.621
WE COULD TURN IT OVER TO CHILD
SERVICES, BUT ONCE THEY'RE IN,

23:18.660 --> 23:21.322
THEY'RE LIKE IN-LAWS.
YOU CAN'T GET RID OF 'EM.

23:21.360 --> 23:23.794
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, WE LEI-T THEM UP NORTH --

23:23.830 --> 23:26.526
THE ONE GOOD THING
ABOUT MOVING TO THE CITY.

23:26.570 --> 23:29.334
THERE ARE OTHER THINGS
TO LOVE ABOUT THE CITY --

23:29.370 --> 23:30.462
CONCRETE AND GRIDLOCK.
YEAH.

23:30.510 --> 23:33.161
WE SHOULDN'T HAVE COME HERE.
WE'RE FAMILY-VALUES PEOPLE.

23:33.210 --> 23:34.973
YEAH.

23:35.010 --> 23:37.808
LLOYD, I DO MY BEST
TO KEEP THIS CITY SAFE.

23:37.850 --> 23:39.772
BUT THE SCHOOLS
ARE A MESS --

23:39.810 --> 23:43.587
GANG VIOLENCE, UNDERAGE
DRINKING, HARD DRUG USE.

23:43.620 --> 23:46.942
AT LEAST THE SCHOOLS NURSES
ARE GIVING OUT CONDOMS.

23:46.990 --> 23:49.584
[ SCOFFS ] THEY SHOULD BE
TEACHING ABSTINENCE. I MEAN,

23:49.620 --> 23:52.384
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY YOU'RE GONNA
STOP UNWANTED PREGNANCIES.

23:52.430 --> 23:54.557
I MEAN, GEEZ, I'M SURE
YOU KNOW ALL ABOUT THAT.

23:54.600 --> 23:55.453
UH, HOW DO YOU MEAN?

23:55.500 --> 23:56.899
THE BREAKDOWN
OF THE FAMILY STRUCTURE

23:56.930 --> 24:00.320
LEADS TO CRIMINAL BEHAVIOR.
YOU DEAL WITH IT EVERY DAY.
RIGHT. YEAH.

24:00.370 --> 24:02.292
NOTHING GOOD EVER CAME
FROM A BROKEN HOME.

24:02.340 --> 24:04.137
THERE'S NO MORE
WAITING UNTIL MARRIAGE.

24:04.170 --> 24:05.467
THESE KIDS ARE HOOKING UP

24:05.510 --> 24:07.705
WITH STRANGERS THEY MET
ON A PHONE APP.

24:07.740 --> 24:10.208
WHY BUY THE COW WHEN YOU CAN
GET THE MILK FOR FREE?

24:10.240 --> 24:11.707
THAT'S NOT HAPPENING
TO HAYLEY.

24:11.750 --> 24:13.240
SO WHAT DO YOU DO --
LOCK 'EM UP?

24:13.280 --> 24:14.542
YOU GO HOME, DETECTIVE,

24:14.580 --> 24:17.310
AND YOU COMMIT TO RAISING
A TRADITIONAL FAMILY,

24:17.350 --> 24:19.784
WHICH IS WHAT I'D LIKE TO DO
RIGHT NOW.

24:24.430 --> 24:26.318
DAD MAKES ME WEAR
THESE DRESSES EVERY DAY,

24:26.360 --> 24:29.420
AND EVERYBODY AT SCHOOL STARTED
CALLING ME GOODY-TWO-SHOES.

24:29.460 --> 24:31.564
SO I LET ALL THE BOYS
LOOK UP THE DRESSES,

24:31.600 --> 24:33.329
AND EVERYONE
STOPPED SAYING IT.

24:33.370 --> 24:34.598
THAT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.562
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

24:38.470 --> 24:39.937
THE GARAGE IS HAUNTED.

24:41.110 --> 24:42.304
HAUNTED HOW?

24:42.340 --> 24:45.878
WHEN I WAS LITTLE,
I WOKE UP ONE TIME,

24:45.910 --> 24:48.174
AND MY DAD SAID
A SURGEON HAD COME

24:48.220 --> 24:50.142
AND SEWN UP A DEMON
INSIDE ME.

24:51.490 --> 24:54.118
[ CHUCKLES ] I KNOW.
IT'S WHAT HE SAID.

24:56.460 --> 24:58.519
HAYLEY, I NEED
TO MAKE A PHONE CALL.

25:07.370 --> 25:08.860
HEY, YOU STILL
HAVE THE DAD?

25:10.470 --> 25:11.459
BARELY.
HOW IS SHE?

25:11.510 --> 25:14.536
[ SIGHS ] THE THINGS
SHE'S SAYING THAT HE DOES --

25:14.580 --> 25:16.969
IT SOUNDS LIKE
SERIOUS PSYCHOLOGICAL ABUSE.

25:17.010 --> 25:19.171
WELL, YOU GOT TO GIVE ME
SOMETHING TO CHARGE HIM WITH.

25:19.210 --> 25:21.519
OTHERWISE, I CAN'T HOLD HIM.
[ SIGHS ] LOOK, HE MAY NOT BE

25:21.550 --> 25:23.177
DOING ANYTHING ILLEGAL,
BUT HAYLEY IS A CHILD.

25:23.220 --> 25:25.347
All right? She can't
protect herself. That's our job.

25:25.390 --> 25:26.584
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
DETECTIVE?

25:26.620 --> 25:29.214
UH, YEAH, I'M GONNA CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK, OKAY? SORRY. THANKS.

25:29.260 --> 25:31.751
LOOK, I-I JUST WANTED TO THANK
YOU FOR FINDING MY DAUGHTER.

25:31.790 --> 25:33.724
YOU'LL -- YOU'LL NEVER KNOW
HOW GRATEFUL I AM.

25:33.760 --> 25:37.321
YEAH. UH, LLOYD, I, UH...

25:37.360 --> 25:39.999
I'M ABOUT TO HAVE,
UH, ONE MYSELF.

25:40.030 --> 25:40.837
OH, YEAH?
YEAH.

25:40.870 --> 25:41.996
YOUR FIRST?
YEAH, MY FIRST.

25:42.040 --> 25:43.496
WOW, YOUR WIFE
MUST BE THRILLED.

25:43.540 --> 25:45.098
OH, SHE'S THRILLED, YEAH.

25:45.140 --> 25:48.803
I GOT TO TELL YOU, I THINK
YOU AND I ARE A LOT ALIKE.

25:48.840 --> 25:52.139
I SEE YOU WITH YOUR BEAUTIFUL
FAMILY, AND IT'S INSPIRING.

25:52.180 --> 25:54.068
SO HOW DO YOU DO IT?

25:54.120 --> 25:56.008
WELL, YOU LISTEN TO ME.

25:56.050 --> 25:58.883
ONE BAD APPLE
CAN SPOIL THE BUNCH.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.717
IF SHE RUNS,
GO GET HER

26:00.760 --> 26:03.285
AND MAKE SURE
SHE NEVER RUNS AGAIN.

26:03.320 --> 26:05.959
SPARE THE ROD,
SPOIL THE CHILD, HUH?

26:05.990 --> 26:07.548
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH PROTECTING

26:07.600 --> 26:08.953
THE SANCTITY
OF YOUR FAMILY.

26:17.810 --> 26:20.005
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

26:21.140 --> 26:24.906
ELLEN, YOU KNOW, THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF...

26:24.950 --> 26:27.669
I MEAN, UNLESS THERE'S SOMETHING
THAT YOU'RE NOT TELLING US.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.075
NO, NO, NO. IT'S FINE.

26:31.120 --> 26:33.315
I HOPE YOU KNOW THAT
IF YOU SUSPECT YOUR CHILDREN

26:33.350 --> 26:35.682
ARE BEING MISTREATED,
IT IS YOUR RESPONSIBILITY

26:35.720 --> 26:38.257
TO REACH OUT TO SOMEBODY
AND ASK FOR HELP.

26:38.290 --> 26:40.019
[ DOOR OPENS ]

26:41.560 --> 26:43.551
OH, HAYLEY! OH!

26:43.600 --> 26:46.091
[ CRYING ]

26:46.130 --> 26:47.392
Hayley: IS HE HOME?

26:47.430 --> 26:48.533
HE'S ON HIS WAY.

26:48.570 --> 26:50.595
SWAREK HAD TO
CUT HIM LOOSE.

26:50.640 --> 26:52.107
YOU CAN'T LEAVE.

26:52.140 --> 26:54.370
MRS. HILL, I KNOW YOU'VE HAD
A ROUGH COUPLE OF DAYS,

26:54.410 --> 26:56.799
BUT WE JUST NEED TO TAKE A LOOK
INSIDE YOUR GARAGE.

26:56.840 --> 26:57.841
THEN WE'LL BE OFF.

26:57.880 --> 27:01.839
I DON'T EVER
GO IN THE GARAGE.

27:06.050 --> 27:07.813
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

27:16.830 --> 27:17.819
Traci: HAYLEY. ..

27:17.870 --> 27:20.896
HE MAKES YOU
SLEEP IN HERE?

27:25.070 --> 27:27.675
[ Weakly ]
MY HUSBAND'S A HUNTER.

27:27.710 --> 27:29.473
THESE ARE...
HUNTING INSTRUMENTS.

27:29.510 --> 27:31.307
ELLEN, IN YOUR
WORST NIGHTMARES,

27:31.350 --> 27:34.615
DID YOU EVER IMAGINE THAT
THIS IS WHERE SHE WAS SLEEPING?

27:34.650 --> 27:37.642
HE EMPTIED THE FREEZER.
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:37.690 --> 27:39.317
[ Shakily] MOM...
YOU HAVE TO TELL HIM

27:39.350 --> 27:41.489
THAT CONNOR AND I SLEPT IN
SEPARATE ROOMS LAST NIGHT, OKAY?

27:41.520 --> 27:44.455
OKAY? YOU HAVE TO TELL
HIM, OR ELSE HE'S GONNA
PUT ME IN THE FREEZER.

27:44.490 --> 27:46.048
HE'S DONE THAT BEFORE?

27:46.090 --> 27:47.921
PLEASE DON'T LET HIM
HURT ME.

27:47.960 --> 27:49.393
HAYLEY, WE'RE NOT GONNA
LET ANYTHING HAPPEN TO YOU.

27:49.430 --> 27:51.762
YOU NEED TO LEAVE.
LLOYD'S GOING TO BE HOME SOON,

27:51.800 --> 27:53.358
AND -- AND HE'LL KNOW
WE WERE IN HERE.

27:53.400 --> 27:55.664
OKAY, HOW ABOUT
WE TAKE YOU SOMEWHERE SAFE...

27:55.700 --> 27:57.463
A HOTEL --
JUST FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

27:57.500 --> 27:58.899
YOU KNOW,
SO THAT WE CAN TALK

27:58.940 --> 28:01.135
WITHOUT WORRYING
ABOUT LLOYD COMING BACK.

28:01.180 --> 28:03.398
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

28:03.440 --> 28:05.476
[ Shakily]
ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

28:05.510 --> 28:06.704
OKAY.

28:06.750 --> 28:09.014
YOU'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING.

28:09.050 --> 28:11.587
HE'S NOT GONNA
SEE IT THAT WAY.

28:11.620 --> 28:12.644
[ SNIFFLES ]

28:12.690 --> 28:14.487
COME ON OUTSIDE, JEREMY!

28:14.520 --> 28:16.818
I'LL GET HIM.
WE'RE LEAVING!

28:18.390 --> 28:19.379
JEREMY?

28:22.160 --> 28:24.219
I WANT TO WAIT FOR DAD.
I'M SORRY, HONEY.

28:24.270 --> 28:27.421
WE CAN'T WAIT.
WE GOT TO GO NOW, OKAY?

28:27.470 --> 28:28.937
TAKE THIS.

28:30.400 --> 28:33.506
Jeremy: CHECK IT OUT.
LOOK HOW MUCH STUFF IS IN THERE.

28:33.540 --> 28:36.771
IT'S AWESOME.
Hayley: I KNOW.
IT'S GOT A MINIBAR.

28:36.810 --> 28:38.846
SO, WE CAN TAKE
WHATEVER WE WANT?

28:38.880 --> 28:41.314
Gail: YEAH, JUST
STAY OFF THE CHEESE PUFFS.

28:41.350 --> 28:43.910
TRUST ME, THAT'S A BELL
YOU CAN'T UNRING.

28:43.950 --> 28:46.589
BUT WE'RE NOT ALLOWED
TO HAVE SODA AT HOME.

28:46.620 --> 28:48.451
WE WON'T SNITCH.

28:48.490 --> 28:50.856
Jeremy: I WANT CHIPS.

28:50.890 --> 28:52.448
HEY.
YEAH, THAT ONE.

28:52.490 --> 28:53.627
SHE'S JUST RESTING.

28:53.660 --> 28:55.093
OKAY.
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

28:55.130 --> 28:57.928
[ SCOFFS ] I WANT TO DRINK
THE WHOLE MINIBAR.

28:57.970 --> 29:00.495
CAN I JUST SAY SOMETHING?

29:00.530 --> 29:03.966
STEVE MEANS A LOT TO LEO.

29:04.010 --> 29:06.638
AND I'M LUCKY
TO HAVE HIM IN MY LIFE

29:06.670 --> 29:09.173
AND THAT HE LOVES ME...
AND MY CHILD.

29:09.210 --> 29:12.646
[ SIGHS ]
I'M TOO TIRED TO SLEEP.

29:12.680 --> 29:13.669
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:13.710 --> 29:16.213
WELL, YOU'VE HAD
A PRETTY EXHAUSTING 24 HOURS.

29:16.250 --> 29:18.741
I HAVEN'T HAD A FULL NIGHT'S
SLEEP IN 16 YEARS.

29:20.790 --> 29:22.109
I HAVE SO MUCH
TO DO AT HOME,

29:22.160 --> 29:24.321
AND LLOYD REALLY VALUES
A HARD DAY'S WORK.

29:27.260 --> 29:30.229
WHY DON'T -- WHY DON'T
WE MOVE IN THERE?

29:30.260 --> 29:31.966
OKAY.

29:34.700 --> 29:36.395
[ SODA POURING ]

29:36.440 --> 29:38.408
Hayley: NOT LIKE THAT, JEREMY.
YOU'RE MAKING A MESS.

29:38.440 --> 29:41.034
[ Chuckling ] WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TAKE -- TAKE THIS ONE

29:41.080 --> 29:42.729
AND THEN POUR IT
OVER THE SINK?

29:42.780 --> 29:45.908
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

29:45.950 --> 29:47.440
YOU GOT TO GO EASY ON HIM.

29:47.480 --> 29:49.038
WHAT?

29:49.080 --> 29:51.389
HE'S JUST A LITTLE KID,
AND HE'S STRUGGLING, TOO.

29:51.420 --> 29:54.287
YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?
MY FATHER DOTES ON HIM.

29:54.320 --> 29:55.810
YEAH, BUT THAT'S NOT
JEREMY'S FAULT.

29:55.860 --> 29:57.782
I'M JUST SAYING THAT
YOU GUYS ARE IN THIS TOGETHER,

29:57.830 --> 29:59.457
SO IT'S JUST WORTH
KEEPING THAT IN MIND.

30:01.530 --> 30:04.169
I DID IT.

30:04.200 --> 30:05.792
PERFECT POUR.

30:07.530 --> 30:10.499
SO...
[ SIGHS ]

30:10.540 --> 30:11.700
HOW DO I FIX THIS?

30:11.740 --> 30:14.629
YOU NEED TO MAKE AN ALLEGATION
OF ABUSE AGAINST YOUR HUSBAND

30:14.680 --> 30:16.170
AND FILE
AN OFFICIAL STATEMENT,

30:16.210 --> 30:18.269
AND THEN WE HAVE THE GROUNDS
TO ARREST HIM.

30:18.310 --> 30:20.369
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]
THEN WHAT?

30:20.410 --> 30:23.208
Traci: WHILE HE'S WAITING
TO POST BAIL,

30:23.250 --> 30:25.184
WE WORK TO GET
A RESTRAINING ORDER.

30:25.220 --> 30:27.882
A PIECE OF PAPER?
HAS THAT EVER WORKED?

30:27.920 --> 30:30.218
WE'LL CALL VICTIM SERVICES.
WE WILL MAKE SURE

30:30.260 --> 30:33.320
THAT YOU HAVE A SPOT IN A SECURE
SHELTER UNTIL THE COURT DATE.

30:33.360 --> 30:34.952
NO, NO, NO.
I CAN'T GO TO A SHELTER.

30:35.000 --> 30:36.024
[ WATER RUNNING ]

30:36.060 --> 30:38.096
I'LL BE HOMELESS,
AND HE'LL END UP WITH THE KIDS.

30:38.130 --> 30:40.166
IT'S JUST WHAT HE SAID
WOULD HAPPEN IF I EVER LEI-T HIM.

30:40.200 --> 30:43.966
HE'S LYING. HE'S PREYING ON YOUR
FEARS SO YOU WON'T LEAVE HIM.

30:44.010 --> 30:46.763
HAYLEY'S, UH, HAVING A BATH.
SHOULD I ORDER A PIZZA?

30:46.810 --> 30:48.072
SURE.
I'D LIKE TO GO HOME.

30:48.110 --> 30:49.600
WHAT?
WE CAN GO BACK...

30:49.640 --> 30:50.948
RIGHT NOW.

30:50.980 --> 30:52.902
Ellen: WE COULD SAY
WE WERE AT THE STORE.

30:52.950 --> 30:54.941
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
Jeremy: HI. OKAY.

30:54.980 --> 30:57.210
NASH, MCNALLY?

30:57.250 --> 30:59.218
IT'S TOO LATE.

30:59.250 --> 31:00.956
WHAT IS IT?

31:00.990 --> 31:03.857
I THINK JEREMY
JUST GAVE AWAY OUR LOCATION.

31:03.890 --> 31:05.858
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

31:05.890 --> 31:09.189
[ CHILDREN SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE ]

31:09.230 --> 31:10.857
1504 --
WE'RE AT THE HILL RESIDENCE.

31:10.900 --> 31:12.458
UH, IT'S BEEN 10 MINUTES.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

31:12.500 --> 31:14.365
LLOYD'S HERE.
EVERYTHING SEEMS QUIET.

31:14.400 --> 31:15.298
UH, HANG ON, HANG ON.

31:15.340 --> 31:16.261
WHERE'S MY FAMILY?

31:16.300 --> 31:18.131
MR. HILL,
YOUR FAMILY'S FINE.

31:18.170 --> 31:19.865
YOU TOOK MY FAMILY?
YOU SEARCHED MY HOUSE?!

31:19.910 --> 31:21.605
Duncan: MR. -- MR. HILL --
DON'T TOUCH ME!

31:21.640 --> 31:23.278
YOU HAVE NO WARRANT!

31:23.310 --> 31:25.870
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT!
YOU STAY THE HELL AWAY FROM US!

31:25.910 --> 31:27.639
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

31:29.420 --> 31:31.183
DUNCAN, GET IN THE CAR.
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS ]

31:31.220 --> 31:32.619
GET IN THE CAR.
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

31:32.650 --> 31:35.687
W-WHERE IS HE GOING?
HE'S GONNA GO
FIND HIS FAMILY.

31:40.930 --> 31:45.697
Nick:
STAFF'S SENDING US TO THE HOTEL
WHERE THEY HAVE THE FAMILY.

31:45.730 --> 31:47.129
APPARENTLY,
THE DAD'S ON A RAMPAGE.

31:47.170 --> 31:48.535
NO PROBLEM.
IT'S PRETTY DEAD HERE.

31:48.570 --> 31:50.561
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]
OH, YEAH? YOU BORED?

31:50.600 --> 31:52.238
I LIKE A LITTLE ACTION.

31:54.580 --> 31:57.231
BUT WHAT'D YOU EXPECT?
YOU TOOK THE BAD-LUCK RADIO.

31:57.280 --> 31:59.942
Man:
1519 -- WE'VE GOT A 911 CALL

31:59.980 --> 32:01.447
TO 158 STROMAN DRIVE.

32:01.480 --> 32:02.617
WE'RE AT 158 STROMAN.

32:02.650 --> 32:04.140
THE CALLER IS A DELIAH FRYE.

32:04.190 --> 32:06.988
SHE SAYS THERE'S AN INTRUDER
ATTACKING HER SON.

32:07.020 --> 32:08.885
[ DELIAH GASPS ]
[ LLOYD GRUNTS ]

32:08.920 --> 32:10.387
CO-CON NOR!
OH, MY GOD!

32:10.420 --> 32:12.422
GET UP!

32:12.460 --> 32:15.725
YOU RUINED MY DAUGHTER!
[ GRUNTING ]

32:15.760 --> 32:17.421
[ Sobbing ]
CONNOR!

32:17.460 --> 32:18.859
HOW DARE YOU?!

32:18.900 --> 32:20.765
[GRUNTS]
HUH, HUH?!

32:20.800 --> 32:21.994
PUNK!

32:22.940 --> 32:26.398
HEY, HEY!
GET OFF HIM, MR. HILL!

32:26.440 --> 32:28.476
STOP MOVING NOW!

32:30.740 --> 32:32.640
STAY BACK.
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME!

32:32.680 --> 32:33.669
CONNOR?

32:33.710 --> 32:36.110
HE'S THE CRIMINAL!
HE'S A PERVERT!

32:36.150 --> 32:39.449
MY DAUGHTER IS 16!
I'M CALLING AN AMBULANCE.

32:39.490 --> 32:40.843
1519 -- WE NEED E.M.S.

32:40.890 --> 32:43.450
I'LL BE BACK FOR YOU.
NO, YOU WON'T.

32:43.490 --> 32:46.152
I'M GONNA DESTROY YOU.

32:54.870 --> 32:56.337
[ BUZZER SOUNDS ]

32:56.370 --> 32:59.407
Sam: FIRST-TIME OFFENDER,
GRIEF-STRICKEN FATHER --

32:59.440 --> 33:01.738
HE'LL PROBABLY
ONLY GET HOUSE ARREST.

33:01.780 --> 33:04.408
WELL, THEN WE CAN ONLY HOPE
THAT MCNALLY AND NASH

33:04.450 --> 33:06.702
ARE MAKING SOME HEAD WAY
WITH THE WIFE.

33:08.120 --> 33:09.212
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

33:09.250 --> 33:11.946
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN MY LIFE,
I THINK...

33:11.990 --> 33:13.412
I COULD BE A GOOD FATHER.

33:13.450 --> 33:16.317
I KNOW I'M NOT GONNA BE
LIKE MY DAD.

33:16.360 --> 33:20.319
OH, DAMN STRAIGHT.
THAT'S BECAUSE OF MCNALLY.

33:20.360 --> 33:22.248
COULDN'T WAIT
TO DO THIS WITH HER.

33:25.530 --> 33:28.658
[ SIGHS ]
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO THIS...

33:28.700 --> 33:29.792
WITH MARLO?

33:29.840 --> 33:31.307
HERE. [ SIGHS ]

33:31.340 --> 33:37.176
THE BEST THING
THAT YOU CAN DO FOR YOUR KID...

33:37.210 --> 33:40.338
THE BEST
IS JUST TO BE HAPPY YOURSELF.

33:40.380 --> 33:42.541
IT TOOK ME A LONG TIME
TO FIGURE THAT OUT.

33:48.690 --> 33:50.749
Ellen: IT'S OKAY, JEREMY.
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

33:50.790 --> 33:55.227
CAN WE GO HOME NOW?
[ SIGHS ] THIS HAS ALL BEEN
TOO MUCH FOR THEM.

33:55.260 --> 33:56.852
I WANT YOU TO TAKE US HOME.

33:56.900 --> 33:59.926
NO, HE'S GOING TO KILL ME IF YOU
TAKE ME BACK. PLEASE, MOM.

33:59.970 --> 34:01.267
OKAY, ELLEN,
YOU CANNOT DO THIS.

34:01.300 --> 34:03.530
LOOK, I KNOW THE IDEA
OF LEAVING YOUR HUSBAND

34:03.570 --> 34:05.435
AND RAISING THESE KIDS
BY YOURSELF

34:05.470 --> 34:08.200
IS OUTSIDE OF THE TRADITIONAL
FAMILY THAT YOU WANT,

34:08.240 --> 34:10.970
BUT THIS IS YOUR FAMILY,
AND YOU NEED TO PROTECT THEM.

34:11.010 --> 34:12.500
Traci:
LET US TAKE YOU SOMEWHERE SAFE.

34:12.550 --> 34:14.711
[ GASPING ] I CAN'T GO BACK.
I CAN'T DO THIS.

34:14.750 --> 34:15.774
YOU'RE RUINISITI‘ICI'T THIS FAMILY.

34:15.820 --> 34:18.209
[ GASPING ]

34:18.920 --> 34:20.911
HAYLEY!
HAYLEY!
HAYLEY!

34:20.950 --> 34:23.384
WHOA! STAY BACK!
THIS IS PECK. WE NEED E.M.S.

34:23.420 --> 34:25.820
AT THE RIDGEWAY HOTEL
ON KINGSTON ROAD.
SHE'LL BE BETTER SOON.

34:25.860 --> 34:27.987
Man: COPY THAT.
MEDICS ARE TWO MINUTES OUT.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

34:28.030 --> 34:29.952
SHE WAS BEING MEAN
LIKE WHEN ZEKE BIT DAD.

34:30.000 --> 34:31.820
ZEKE? YOUR DOG?

34:31.870 --> 34:34.088
WE GAVE ZEKE THE STUFF IN THE
BLUE BOX TO TEACH HIM A LESSON.

34:34.140 --> 34:36.836
[ GASPS ]

34:36.870 --> 34:39.134
[ WHIMPERING ]

34:39.170 --> 34:41.775
TERMINATOX?
THIS IS PEST POISON.

34:41.810 --> 34:43.903
[ GASPS ]
WHAT HAVE YOU --

34:43.940 --> 34:46.340
OH, MY --
OH, DEAR GOD!

34:46.380 --> 34:49.042
[ CRYING ]

34:49.080 --> 34:51.287
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

34:57.260 --> 35:02.653
Traci:
SO, YOU BROUGHT STUFF FROM HOME
TO PUT IN YOUR SISTER'S DRINK?

35:02.700 --> 35:07.091
ZEKE WAS OUT OF CONTROL, SO
DAD SENT HIM TO A BETTER PLACE.

35:07.130 --> 35:10.566
HAYLEY'S WORSE, RIGHT?
SHE'S RUINING OUR FAMILY.

35:10.600 --> 35:12.409
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER
CONTINUES ]

35:12.440 --> 35:14.908
UH, JEREMY,
THIS IS LORI KAVANAGH

35:14.940 --> 35:16.237
FROM CHILD SERVICES.

35:16.280 --> 35:18.840
I WANT YOU TO TELL HER
THE WHOLE STORY,

35:18.880 --> 35:22.646
ABOUT YOUR DAD, ABOUT ZEKE --
ABOUT EVERYTHING, OKAY?

35:22.680 --> 35:23.772
OKAY.

35:23.820 --> 35:25.742
HI, JEREMY.
HI.

35:33.360 --> 35:35.453
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER,
CAR HORN HONKS ]

35:35.500 --> 35:37.593
IS SHE GOING TO BE
ALL RIGHT?

35:37.630 --> 35:39.518
Paramedic:
WE NEED TO TAKE HER TO MEMORIAL.

35:39.570 --> 35:41.788
THEY'LL HAVE TO REPEAT
THE VOMITING INDUCTION

35:41.840 --> 35:43.432
AND CHARCOAL
EVERY FOUR HOURS.

35:43.470 --> 35:44.562
THANK YOU.

35:44.610 --> 35:46.339
OKAY, WE'LL FOLLOW
IN MY CAR.

35:46.370 --> 35:48.235
GAIL'S GONNA BE WITH HER
THE WHOLE TIME.

35:48.280 --> 35:49.235
[ SIREN WAILING ]

35:49.280 --> 35:50.872
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO JEREMY?

35:52.210 --> 35:54.474
UH, I MEAN, HE'S GONNA HAVE TO
TAKE A PSYCH EVALUATION

35:54.520 --> 35:57.011
TO DETERMINE WHETHER HE'S
DANGEROUS FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

35:57.050 --> 35:59.211
ARE THEY GONNA
TAKE HIM AWAY?

36:01.290 --> 36:02.655
YOU KNOW, JEREMY
WAS ONLY DOING

36:02.690 --> 36:04.624
WHAT HIS FATHER
TAUGHT HIM WAS RIGHT.

36:04.660 --> 36:05.820
IF YOU WANT HIM BACK,

36:05.860 --> 36:08.624
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO PROVE
THAT YOU CAN TAKE CONTROL

36:08.660 --> 36:09.695
AND LEAD THIS FAMILY.

36:11.300 --> 36:14.497
I WAS 16
WHEN I MARRIED LLOYD.

36:14.540 --> 36:15.632
[ SNIFFLES ]

36:15.670 --> 36:18.434
I WAS SO YOUNG, MY PARENTS
HAD TO SIGN OVER CUSTODY.

36:19.470 --> 36:21.904
I KNOW THIS ISN'T
THE FAMILY THAT YOU PICTURED.

36:21.940 --> 36:25.376
BUT IT'S THE ONE YOU HAVE.
AND YOU DO HAVE A CHOICE.

36:28.580 --> 36:31.583
I'LL TESTIFY AGAINST LLOYD.
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

36:31.620 --> 36:35.386
I'LL DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO KEEP JEREMY AND HAYLEY SAFE.

36:35.420 --> 36:37.251
GOOD.

36:47.970 --> 36:49.494
WHAT'S WRONG?

36:49.540 --> 36:51.428
[ SIGHS ]

36:51.470 --> 36:54.030
I'VE SPENT ALL DAY
ON THE DARK WEB.

36:54.070 --> 36:56.072
I'VE READ BLURBS ONLINE
ABOUT HIT MEN

36:56.110 --> 36:57.634
THAT READ
LIKE DATING PROFILES.

36:57.680 --> 36:59.875
I NOW KNOW
HOW TO SKYPE A THAI HOOKER

36:59.910 --> 37:02.470
IF I EVER FEEL SO INCLINED.

37:02.520 --> 37:06.217
BUT I COULDN'T FIND
A SINGLE CONNECTION

37:06.250 --> 37:09.310
TO ANYBODY THAT SELLS
INDUSTRIAL EXPLOSIVES

37:09.360 --> 37:11.988
AND ANYBODY WE ARRESTED THE DAY
THE EVIDENCE ROOM BLEW UP.

37:12.030 --> 37:13.986
REALLY?

37:14.030 --> 37:15.429
I WAS DISAPPOINTED.
I THOUGHT --

37:15.460 --> 37:17.451
I LIKE INTELLIGENCE,
I LIKE WORKING WITH YOU,

37:17.500 --> 37:20.765
BUT MAYBE
I'M JUST NOT CUT OUT FOR THIS.

37:20.800 --> 37:22.495
UNTIL...

37:22.540 --> 37:24.508
UNTIL?

37:24.540 --> 37:27.065
MEET CHRIS KLEM,
AN INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR

37:27.110 --> 37:29.135
WITH A LICENSE
TO SELL EXPLOSIVES.

37:29.180 --> 37:33.048
ONE OF HIS SUPPLIERS --
FRACK MANUFACTURING.

37:33.080 --> 37:35.116
OKAY, HAS HE EVER SOLD

37:35.150 --> 37:37.118
TO ANYONE
THAT WE ARRESTED THAT DAY

37:37.150 --> 37:39.038
OR SOMEONE
WHO'S CONNECTED TO THEM?

37:39.090 --> 37:39.840
NO.

37:39.890 --> 37:42.882
THE CONNECTION
GOES DEEPER THAN THAT.

37:42.920 --> 37:46.856
HE SUPPLIES EXPLOSIVES TO THE
METROPOLITAN POLICE DEPARTMENT.

37:46.890 --> 37:48.448
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

37:48.500 --> 37:50.320
HE'S BASICALLY
THE GUY THE COPS CALL

37:50.360 --> 37:52.123
IF THEY WANT
TO BLOW SOMETHING UP.

37:52.170 --> 37:53.194
OH, DOV, THIS IS BAD.

37:53.230 --> 37:55.892
IT GETS WORSE.
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

37:55.940 --> 37:57.862
HE DISAPPEARED. ..

37:57.900 --> 37:59.936
WHAT?
...THREE WEEKS AGO.

37:59.970 --> 38:03.770
THIS IS THE MISSING-PERSONS
REPORT FROM THE KITCHENER P.D.

38:03.810 --> 38:05.175
OKAY, SO, WAIT A MINUTE.

38:05.210 --> 38:06.245
SO YOU'RE SAYING TO ME

38:06.280 --> 38:08.748
THAT THE ONLY GUY
THAT WE CAN CONNECT TO THAT BOMB

38:08.780 --> 38:11.613
IS THE SAME GUY WHO SELLS
EXPLOSIVES TO THE POLICE?

38:14.490 --> 38:16.617
WE NEED TO FIND CHRIS KLEM.

38:22.230 --> 38:23.754
HEY, NICE WORK TODAY,
WARD.

38:23.800 --> 38:24.960
YOU, TOO, COLLINS.

38:25.000 --> 38:27.992
IT'S GOOD TO SEE THE BAD-LUCK
RADIO WORKED OUT FOR YOU.

38:29.240 --> 38:31.800
COLLINS, UM...

38:31.840 --> 38:34.206
I DIDN'T TAKE
THE BAD-LUCK RADIO.

38:34.240 --> 38:35.309
I KNOW.
[ PEN CLICKS ]

38:35.340 --> 38:38.002
WOULD'VE SHORTED OUT ON YOU
BY NOW.

38:38.040 --> 38:40.679
[ SCOFFS ]

38:40.710 --> 38:43.474
YOU KNOW, WE CAN'T
GO FOR BEERS, BUT...

38:43.520 --> 38:46.887
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THAT I'M NOT INTERESTED.

38:48.960 --> 38:50.086
...IN WHAT YOU HAVE TO SAY,

38:50.120 --> 38:53.783
'CAUSE I THINK YOU SAID YOU'RE
A WISE, OLD OWL OR WHATEVER.

38:53.830 --> 38:56.526
PERSON OF WISDOM, BUT YEAH.
RIGHT, RIGHT.

38:56.560 --> 38:58.767
WELL, HAVE A GREAT NIGHT.

39:03.040 --> 39:05.361
[ SIGHS ]

39:07.310 --> 39:09.403
DID YOU BREAK UP WITH HER?
WHA-- I'M...

39:09.440 --> 39:10.805
GOING TO DO THAT RIGHT NOW.

39:10.840 --> 39:13.547
WHY DO YOU SMELL
LIKE SEX COLOGNE, DIAZ?
WHAT?

39:13.580 --> 39:17.038
DIAZ, CAN I TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THE THING WE DISCUSSED?

39:21.760 --> 39:24.149
I'M SORRY, SIR.
IT'S A...

39:24.190 --> 39:25.418
LOAD-BEARING WALL.

39:25.460 --> 39:28.156
OH, WELL. YOU WIN SOME,
AND YOU LOSE SOME.

39:28.190 --> 39:29.794
HOW'D
THAT BUDGET MEETING GO?

39:31.030 --> 39:33.828
THEY WANT ME TO MAKE A 15%
EMPLOYMENT CUT AT THIS DIVISION.

39:33.870 --> 39:36.088
WHAT?
BUT I TOLD THEM
THESE ARE MY PEOPLE,

39:36.140 --> 39:39.234
AND I'M NOT GONNA REWARD
HARD WORK WITH UNEMPLOYMENT.

39:39.270 --> 39:40.237
YOU -- YOU SAID THAT?

39:40.270 --> 39:41.476
[ CHUCKLES ]

39:41.510 --> 39:44.900
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE ME, RIGHT?
I'M A BOTTOM-LINE KIND OF A GUY.

39:44.950 --> 39:47.908
WELL...THAT DOESN'T MATTER TO ME
AS MUCH THESE DAYS.

39:47.950 --> 39:51.374
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING, DIAZ.

39:51.420 --> 39:55.789
LATELY, MY WIFE
HAS BEEN, UH...

39:55.820 --> 39:58.755
WELL, LET'S JUST SAY
HAPPY WIFE, HAPPY LIFE.

40:01.500 --> 40:03.422
OFFICER PECK.

40:06.400 --> 40:08.937
I-I GOT TO
KEEP SEEING HER.
YOU'RE AN IDIOT.

40:08.970 --> 40:11.097
WHAT?
I JUST SAVED EVERYONE'S JOB!

40:11.140 --> 40:12.129
WH--

40:14.780 --> 40:18.648
* NOBODY WANTS A THING

40:18.680 --> 40:22.548
* WELL, YOU AREN'T THERE
TO DIE ALONE *

40:22.580 --> 40:26.346
* NOBODY NEEDS TO BREAK DOWN

40:26.390 --> 40:30.110
* WE JUST NEED A HAND TO HOLD

40:37.300 --> 40:40.292
YOU DESERVE
THE PERFECT FAMILY.

40:40.330 --> 40:46.360
AND MORE THAN ANYTHING, THAT --
I WANTED YOU AND I TO HAVE THAT.

40:46.410 --> 40:48.139
AND NOW I CAN'T
GIVE THAT TO YOU.

40:50.480 --> 40:52.368
[Voice breaking ]
DID I WANT TO BE

40:52.410 --> 40:57.040
THE WOMAN
TO MAKE YOU A FATHER?

40:57.080 --> 40:59.878
YES.

40:59.920 --> 41:01.410
AND WHEN YOU...

41:01.450 --> 41:02.610
SAW YOUR CHILD...

41:02.660 --> 41:04.287
* SO KEEP LOOKING FOR A WAY

41:04.320 --> 41:05.628
* ANOTHER CHANCE
TO START AGAIN *

41:05.660 --> 41:09.756
...DID I WANT YOU TO SEE
A MIXTURE OF ME AND YOU

41:09.800 --> 41:13.099
IN A PERFECT, LITTLE
HUMAN BEING?

41:13.130 --> 41:15.394
YEAH.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.567
BUT JUST BECAUSE
THIS ISN'T...

41:17.600 --> 41:22.799
WHAT I PICTURED,
IT DOESN'T MEAN I FOLD. OKAY?

41:22.840 --> 41:25.638
* I'M GONNA HOLD YOU CLOSE

41:25.680 --> 41:29.377
I HAVE NO IDEA
HOW TO DO THIS.

41:29.420 --> 41:31.513
AND I KNOW
IT'S NOT GONNA BE EASY.

41:31.550 --> 41:33.643
* IT HURTS TOO MUCH

41:33.690 --> 41:37.387
BUT WHAT I CAN SAY...
* AND IT CAN GO WRONG

41:37.420 --> 41:39.081
...IS THAT I LOVE YOU.

41:39.130 --> 41:42.054
* I'M GONNA HOLD YOU

41:42.100 --> 41:46.389
AND I WILL SHOW UP.
AND WE'RE GONNA FIGURE THIS OUT.

41:46.430 --> 41:48.739
*OH

41:48.770 --> 41:50.988
I PROMISE YOU
THERE IS NOT GONNA BE A DAY

41:51.040 --> 41:55.670
WHERE THAT CHILD DOES NOT
FEEL WANTED OR LOVED BY ME.

41:55.710 --> 41:58.747
* I'M GONNA HOLD YOU CLOSE

41:58.780 --> 41:59.542
OKAY.

41:59.580 --> 42:01.275
* I'M GONNA HOLD YOU

42:01.310 --> 42:05.519
* OH, I'M GONNA HOLD YOU CLOSE
